YG HR Web App

This project is a simple staff HR web app connected to Google Sheets.

Main links

Web app:
https://yogurutotopssathupradit-creator.github.io/yg-hr/

Google Sheet:
https://docs.google.com/spreadsheets/d/1P9Hl80PDTMGWq0s5ztlVGp4pAWE4EdFs1qHLXwwa8og/edit?usp=sharing

Apps Script Web App:
https://script.google.com/macros/s/AKfycbxPwTQW5BL9yMZhbkCfe_br1CPU6mjBiw1nJ-1N3v6H1rDAlW1-0kEoEA32K9ohwIkcMg/exec


How it works

1. Staff open the web app on their phone.
2. The web app sends requests to Apps Script.
3. Apps Script reads and writes data in the Google Sheet.
4. The Google Sheet is the main database.


Where to edit data

Employee names:
Edit the "พนักงาน" tab.
Only rows with "ตำแหน่ง" set to "พนักงาน" will appear in the web app.

Check-in and check-out records:
Saved in the "เช็คอิน-เอาท์" tab.

Leave requests:
Saved in the "ลางาน" tab.
New requests are inserted at the top of the request table, newest first.
Admin can change the status in the sheet.
The submitted date includes the time, so requests can be sorted by when staff sent them.
When status is "อนุมัติ", the yearly leave quota tab is updated automatically.
If admin changes it back to "รออนุมัติ", "ไม่อนุมัติ", or "ยกเลิก", the quota is recalculated and restored.
The "โควต้า(วัน)" columns stay as the yearly allowance.
The "ใช้ไป" and "คงเหลือ" columns are the numbers that update.

OT requests:
Saved in the "โอที" tab.
New requests are inserted at the top of the request table, newest first.
Admin can change the status in the sheet.
The "เวลาที่ยื่น" column shows when staff sent the OT request.

Schedule:
Edit the "ตารางกะ" tab.
The web app only shows schedule data. Do not edit schedule settings from the web app.
To lock one staff member to a position or shift, edit these columns in the "พนักงาน" tab:
- "ตำแหน่งหลัก"
- "กะหลัก"

Leave those cells blank, or type "หมุนเวียน", to let the system rotate automatically.

Public holidays:
Edit the "วันหยุดนักขัตฤกษ์" tab.

Monthly salary summary:
Saved in the "สรุปเงินเดือน" tab.
Apps Script updates it automatically on the 28th of every month.
The app calculates work days, approved leave, unpaid leave, holiday work, OT, normal pay, special holiday pay, and net total.
"เบี้ยขยัน" and "Incentive" are not auto-calculated. Admin can fill those in manually, and the next salary sync keeps those values.


Important rules

Do not rename sheet tabs unless the code is also updated.

When adding a new employee, make sure:
- Name is in the "ชื่อ" column.
- Position is exactly "พนักงาน".
- OT rate is filled in the "อัตราโอที/ชม." column.
- Day off is filled in the "วันหยุดประจำ" column.

If the employee does not appear in the web app, check that the position is exactly:
พนักงาน


When code changes

If index.html changes:
Push the file to GitHub so GitHub Pages updates the web app.

If Apps Script changes:
You must deploy a new Apps Script version.

Steps:
1. Open Apps Script.
2. Paste the updated Apps Script code.
3. Click Deploy > Manage deployments.
4. Edit the Web App deployment.
5. Choose New version.
6. Click Deploy.

Just clicking Run is not enough for the live web app.


Apps Script deployment settings

Execute as:
Me

Who has access:
Anyone

The Google Sheet itself can remain private. Apps Script is the public gate that the web app uses.


Automatic jobs

After deploying Apps Script, run this function once in Apps Script:
setAllTriggers

You do not need to manually run the quota sync after approving leave.
When admin edits the "ลางาน" tab, the quota is recalculated automatically.

This creates:
- weekly schedule auto-fill
- leave quota sync every 10 minutes
- leave quota sync when the sheet is edited
- salary summary on the 28th of every month


Security note

The app uses a shared secret token to block casual access to the Apps Script API.

This is basic protection only. A technical person could still inspect the web app code. For stronger protection, add employee PINs or Google login later.
